 from lzahas acs two bu edu lukas zahas subject re how do di boxes work organization boston university boston ma usa lines one nine in article lancer oconnor wpi edu stephe lewis foskett writes i m doing sound for a couple of bands around here and we need direct input boxes for the keyboards these are the little boxes that take a line level out of the keyboard and transform it into low z for the run to the mixer sadly they cost like five zero or more each and i m going to need like five or one zero of them i looked inside one belonging to another band and it looks like just a transformer does anyone have any plans for building them five zero each don t bother trying to make one yourself just shop around a little i ve found dod brand di boxes for as cheap as two zero each you can get higher end ones for more but for pa use for bands i wouldn t bother making one yourself might work but getting a sturdy enough enclosure might be hard they re made of heavy guage metal since they re always on the floor being kicked around a lot for any additional questions on this topic you might want to post to rec audio pro lukas zahas lzahas bu edu